T1  - REVEALED PREFERENCE AND ACTIVITY RULES IN DYNAMIC AUCTIONS
AU  - Ausubel, Lawrence M.
AU  - Baranov, Oleg
Y1  - 2020/05/01
PY  - 2020
DA  - 2020/05/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1111/iere.12431
T2  - International Economic Review
JF  - International Economic Review
JO  - International Economic Review
JA  - International Economic Review
SP  - 471
EP  - 502
VL  - 61
IS  - 2
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0020-6598
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/iere.12431
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - Abstract Activity rules?constraints that limit bidding in future rounds based on past bids?are intended to limit strategic bidding delays in high-stakes auctions. This article provides a general treatment of activity rules. Traditional point-based rules are effective for homogeneous goods and reasonably suited for substitute goods. However, they are simultaneously too strong and too weak for general environments; they allow parking, while sometimes preventing straightforward bidding. We prove that the activity rule operationalizing the generalized axiom of revealed preference (GARP) is essentially the unique rule that enforces the Law of Demand while enabling straightforward bidding and never producing ?dead ends.?
ER  - 

TY  - JOUR
T1  - SYSTEMATIC MONETARY POLICY AND THE MACROECONOMIC EFFECTS OF SHIFTS IN RESIDENTIAL LOAN-TO-VALUE RATIOS
AU  - Bachmann, Rüdiger
AU  - Rüth, Sebastian K.
Y1  - 2020/05/01
PY  - 2020
DA  - 2020/05/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1111/iere.12432
T2  - International Economic Review
